{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2024-2267","published":"2024-10-18T11:09:24Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:20:47.184589Z","upstream":["CVE-2024-8612"],"summary":"qemu security update","details":"QEMU is a FAST! processor emulator using dynamic translation to achieve good emulation speed.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nA flaw was found in QEMU, in the virtio-scsi, virtio-blk, and virtio-crypto devices. The size for virtqueue_push as set in virtio_scsi_complete_req / virtio_blk_req_complete / virito_crypto_req_complete could be larger than the true size of the data which has been sent to guest. Once virtqueue_push() finally calls dma_memory_unmap to ummap the in_iov, it may call the address_space_write function to write back the data. Some uninitialized data may exist in the bounce.buffer, leading to an information leak.(CVE-2024-8612)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"qemu","ecosystem":"openEuler:22.03-LTS-SP3","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/qemu&distro=openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP3"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["qemu-6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","qemu-block-curl-6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","qemu-block-iscsi-6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","qemu-block-rbd-6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","qemu-block-ssh-6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","qemu-debuginfo-6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","qemu-debugsource-6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","qemu-guest-agent-6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","qemu-hw-usb-host-6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","qemu-img-6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","qemu-system-aarch64-6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","qemu-system-arm-6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","qemu-system-riscv-6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","qemu-system-x86_64-6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm"],"noarch":["qemu-help-6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3.noarch.rpm"],"src":["qemu-6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["qemu-6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3.x86_64.rpm","qemu-block-curl-6.2.0-100.oe2203sp3.x86_64.r